Implemented a spec-critical slice of the refactor in the shared sync layer and CLI wiring.

In [sync-node.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.ts:226) I added real token-permission enforcement for `read`/`write`/`admin` operations, exposed parsed claims, scoped `listSessions()` for session tokens, and implemented actual per-session `localId` dedup so replayed logical messages do not duplicate state. I covered that in [sync-node.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.test.ts:14).

I also moved session-token minting into a dedicated helper at [syncNodeToken.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/api/syncNodeToken.ts:1), updated the SyncNode-based runners to import that helper directly, and changed the CLI public surface in [lib.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/lib.ts:8) to export `SyncBridge` plus the token helper instead of exporting the legacy `ApiSessionClient`.

Verified:
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync typecheck`
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:unit`
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:integration`
- `yarn workspace happy-coder typecheck`
- `yarn workspace happy-coder test src/api/apiSession.test.ts src/codex/utils/v3Mapper.test.ts`

The wider refactor described in the plan still has remaining legacy consumer code in the app and some agent paths, but the shared SyncNode contract is now materially closer to the spec.
